Hi @elrumordelaluz thing is that I am using [css-modules](https://github.com/css-modules/css-modules). So I am not able to simply write something like `class="shake-constant"` in my markup. Also all my class names will be hashed on deployment and I do not load any plain CSS files from my server. So what I basically do (in the project using my fork) is:

``` scss
@import "../../../node_modules/csshake/scss/csshake";

.callToActionShaking {
  @extend .callToAction;
  @extend .shake-constant;

  display: block;
}
```

That's why I need `shake-constant` to be defined ;-)
. Yes I tried that but then I am only able to get the shake effect on hover.
. The first one works, thanks!
